data.title: EDITORIAL: Junior partner
data.meta_description: Remember Robert F. Kennedy Jr., member of perhaps the country's most famous political family, who brought us whopper conspiracy theories that suggest chemicals in our water are turning our kids transgender, among others? You know, the guy with the dead worm in his head? And yesterday some nonsense came over the wire about a dead bear cub in Central Park? Is this a presidential campaign or a bad soap opera?
